               <floruit notBefore="1400" precision="medium">The Stephanites were a religious movement within Ethiopian monasticism named after their
                  founder and spiritual leader <roleName type="title">ʾabbā</roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS3894estifano">ʾƎsṭifānos</persName>. 
                  The movement rose to prominence in the 15th century and continued until the 16th century. They were persecuted under the order of 
                  <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> 
                  <persName ref="PRS10626ZaraY">Zarʾa Yāʿqob</persName>. 
                  The Stephanites contributed considerably for the literary production in medieval Ethiopia.
               </floruit>
